text: Sandy Iannella (born 6 April 1987) is an Italian footballer who plays as a striker for Sassuolo. She used to play for LivornoProfile in Football.it and Torres. Iannella was released by Cuneo. She then joined Sassuolo on 7 August. She played on the women's u19 national team and the senior national team.Profile in UEFA.comProfile in Global Sports Archive ==Competitions won== * Serie A: 2009–10, 2010–11, 2011–12, 2012–13 * Coppa Italia: 2007–08, 2010–11 * Suppercoppa Italiana: 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013 * Italy Women's Cup: 2008 ==References== Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Footballers from Tuscany Category:Sportspeople from Livorno
